      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">86/07/26 ¶  ¶ I was pleasingly surprised, dear Dr Beccari, to receive together ¶  ¶ two ¶  ¶ parts of your admirable ¶  ¶ "Malesia" ¶  ¶ by last mail, ¶ Beccari (1877-90): last part of vol.2 and first...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.07.26c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Odoardo Beccari</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">University of Florence, Science Library: Botany, Archives, Beccari 12/32.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">86/07/26</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was pleasingly surprised, dear Dr Beccari, to receive together<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">two</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>parts of your admirable<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"Malesia"<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by last mail,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Beccari (1877-90): last part of vol.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>2 and first part<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of vol.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>3;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 26 July 1886<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 86-07-26b).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and beg to thank you for your generous sending; it will be for my private library, but I always order also a copy through Dulan &amp; Co for my Department, so that I have tw[o]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition</seg>: MS damaged. All [ ] <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in the letter have this meaning.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sets of this important work. Your learned es[say] on the ant-plants h[as] now come to a worth[y] conclusion.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am not surprised [that] our friend Baron C[esati] and myself have [not al]ways recognized the [New] Guinea ferns with absolute correctness, or viewed them in Hookers and Bakers limitation.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M's main treatment of the Papuan ferns is in B76.12.03, pp 76–82. See also<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>W.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Hooker<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Baker (1865-68) and later editions (see TL2, publication No. 3024).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Indeed Darwinism leads to Jordanism! (entre nous).<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>'Critical botany … has … been exaggerated by Alexis Jordan and his followers into an impracticable and futile extreme'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(B.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Jackson<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(1881), p. xxxviii). But<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see notes to M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 25 July 1885.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— Both Cesati and myself may in some cases have trusted too implicitly to incorrectly named Asiatic and other specimens of ferns in our collections for comparison. At the whole, he as well as I, have come fairly near the truth in our identifications. — But you will wonder why I did not, when resuming the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"Papuan Plants"<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for elaborating the plants of Capt Everills &amp; Mr Forbes's Expeditions refer to Cesati's memoir.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Royal Geographical Society of Australasia's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>expedition to the Fly River,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>led by Henry Everill; Henry Forbes's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>highland expedition partially supported by the Society.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Cesati (1877). M resumed his series on Papuan plants in B85.06.03.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This is easily ex[plained ….]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[…] in this paragraph and the next indicates missing text, where the corner of MS is missing.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>published D'Alber[tis …] towards the end o[f …] and Cesati publis[hed …] in Febr<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">1877</hi>
               </seg>. — In […] I explored at Shar[k Bay…] and in other parts […] Australia;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M visited WA, including Shark's Bay, in 1877.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and th[…] essay of our lamen[ted …] must have come, w[…] I was away. In all […]lity, when among th[…] of accumulated prints on my return I glanced merely on the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"Prospetto", I was<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">misled</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by the word<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"Polinesia"<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in the title, as New Guinea is not strictly Polynesian. Soon after in 1877 I became<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">very ill,</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for a long time, in 1878 I moved into new quarters with library &amp;c &amp;c; — in 1879 we had to commence the heavy extra-work for the [… Melb]ourne exhibition<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>International Exhibition, Melbourne, 1880-1.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[… i]n which also Italy [… sp]lendidly represented. [… los]t sight of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"Prospetto"<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[…]ur, and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">hunted</hi>
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>it […]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">now</hi>
               </seg>, when I saw […]oted by Baker<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Baker (1886).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and […]elf in the 3th<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn9" n="10">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>3<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">over</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>5.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>vol […M]alesia. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I shall cer[tainly] explain this unin[tentio]nal shortcoming in the forthcoming (almost<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ready</hi>
               </seg>) 9th number of the Papuan Plants.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn10" n="11">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B90.05.01. M did not mention Cesati in the introduction to this part, which did not contain any ferns.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Before I leave this subject I like to remark, that I by no means concur in all the limitations of our friend Baker, who likes to keep up Nephrodium, Nephrolepis, Gymnogramme in due piety to Hooker senior though we should<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"numquam in verba magistri jurare"<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn11" n="12">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Never swear by the words of the master.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— Exempli causa take Schizaea dichotoma; how can be united to it S. Forsteri, which both Sprengel and Willdenow clearly defined in the beginning of the century. As Mr Baker never saw a[…] Schizea in a wild sta[te] he may be easily misl[ed] though S. Forsteri be[longs] almost to the section [Ac]tinostachys, as I poin[ted out] in Campbell's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"New [Hebri]des",<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn12" n="13">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B73.13.01, p. 27. The point was not made explicitly, but implied by the discussion.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of which work I […] gave you a copy. — It will be worth your while, [to in]vestigate this Sch[izea] question independen[tly] in Italy; the two c[…] distinguished at a glance! but S. bifida is only a small form of S. dichotoma, as any one can see on the heathground near Melbourne. Kindly tell me the results of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">your</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>examination, as this matter should be cleared up, after the error has been continued in the Malesia.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn13" n="14">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Beccari (1877-90), vol. 3, p. 52. In M's copy of the work, now in the library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne, he has written an emphatic 'No!' at the point where<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Schizaea dichotoma</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">S. Forsteri</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>are united.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will at last receive the volume on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"Myoporinous plants"<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with 76 quarto-plates, its issue being long delayed at the binders establishment.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn14" n="15">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B86.08.05. The indexes list 72 numbered plates plus two supplemental plates, consistent with the content of copies seen.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The incessant demands [y]ear after year on my Department for the successive great Exhibitions,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn15" n="16">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Gillbank (2008).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has much hindered my Museum-work; but the sorting of spare specimens is now under progress, and you will therefore soon get something in return for your Sumatran plants.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn16" n="17">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to O. Beccari, 5 February 1880.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>And now my dear Dr Becari, I bid you<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"adieu"<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— I am suffering much from pulmonary inflammation, and even if that does not carry me off soon, — at best there can be little time left of my earthly career! If I can identify my name yet with some Papuan plants I shall be thankful to my generous friends like your self and then my bid<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn17" n="18">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>bit?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of earthly task<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">is done</hi>
               </seg>!</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Your Agapetes seem to me deserving a distinct generic place; the biformous anthers are quite peculiar, so far as my researches go, and bring them near Macleania Can you kindly tell me the year, when Marsigli<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn18" n="19">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Marsili? Marsili (1786).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>published Firmiana, a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">good</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>genus. How can species with superior and inferior radicle be put into<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">one</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>genus!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>What a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">pity</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that Baker made a new fern genus on so trifling ground; the difference is not such as between Alsophila and Polypodium.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn19" n="20">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Written in the centre margin between pp.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>2 and 3, adjacent to the end of the discussion on p. 2 of Cesati's and M's treatment of ferns.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Triphlebia</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was erected in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Beccari<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(1877-90),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>vol.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>3,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>p. 41.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I notice a printing error, Angiopteris<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">erecta</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>instead evecta<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn20" n="21">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Written in the margin of p. 5;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Beccari (1877-90), vol. 3, p. 52.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
